-- Chinese Finance Ministry Sells 182-Day Bills at 1.92% Yield, Traders Say
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-09T02:37:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/chinese-finance-ministry-sells-182-day-bills-at-1-92-yield-traders-say.html

          
          
             China’s finance ministry sold 20
billion yuan ($2.95 billion) of 182-day bills at an average
yield of 1.9256 percent, according to traders at the Industrial &
Commercial Bank of China Ltd. and Bank of China Ltd. in Beijing.  
 The average yield compared with the 1.9616 percent yield in
secondary-market trading yesterday, according to rates compiled
by Chinabond, the nation’s biggest debt-clearing house. The
government last sold similar-maturity bills May 14 at 1.54
percent.  
